1
00:00:05,842 --> 00:00:08,833
When I would sometimes,
with Guru Mahārāj,

2
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:10,134
allow my intellect

3
00:00:10,134 --> 00:00:12,281
[Naked Mother Logic]

4
00:00:12,281 --> 00:00:16,218
and analytical abilities
to get the upper hand

5
00:00:16,219 --> 00:00:19,134
and start 
an A+B=C kind of thing

6
00:00:19,134 --> 00:00:22,911
about some exalted 
devotee’s background,

7
00:00:22,911 --> 00:00:26,258
once, Guru Mahārāj said,

8
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:31,082
“You’re going to break your head
if you keep thinking like this.”

9
00:00:31,082 --> 00:00:38,917
He said, “Actually, we want to be
in a position to receive their grace.”

10
00:00:38,963 --> 00:00:43,552
So we don’t want to look too far
in the background,

11
00:00:43,573 --> 00:00:48,443
and this is the difference between
spiritual culture and material culture

12
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:52,635
because this is 
the cultivation of faith.

13
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:56,081
So, an example is given
to help us understand this,

14
00:00:56,094 --> 00:00:58,445
because we have a tendency
to put all the emphasis

15
00:00:58,445 --> 00:01:02,369
on objective reality
and ignore the subjective aspect,

16
00:01:02,369 --> 00:01:06,178
when spiritual culture puts
the maximum amount of emphasis

17
00:01:06,178 --> 00:01:12,137
on the subjective aspect,
while de–emphasising the objective.

18
00:01:12,137 --> 00:01:18,136
So, what do the Nyāya,
the books of logic say?

19
00:01:18,136 --> 00:01:20,700
Nagna-mātṛkā-nyāya.

20
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,678
This is a fault in thinking,
and what is it called?

21
00:01:23,678 --> 00:01:28,675
The fault of 
the naked mother logic.

22
00:01:28,675 --> 00:01:31,677
And what it means is,
if you have a child

23
00:01:31,677 --> 00:01:33,620
—there’s your mother, 
you’re a child—

24
00:01:33,620 --> 00:01:39,176
and the child starts thinking,
“My mother was once a naked girl.”

25
00:01:39,176 --> 00:01:41,385
So, instead of seeing her as mother,

26
00:01:41,385 --> 00:01:43,579
the nourishing mother figure
and all that,

27
00:01:43,579 --> 00:01:48,529
—which is true, the actual reality
at the present—

28
00:01:48,529 --> 00:01:50,138
if we look in the background 
and say,

29
00:01:50,138 --> 00:01:53,396
“Yes, but she was once 
a naked girl”

30
00:01:53,396 --> 00:01:55,578
and you think of her in that way,

31
00:01:55,578 --> 00:01:57,715
there’s some fault on your part.

32
00:01:57,715 --> 00:02:02,115
And even though it may be
technically, objectively true,

33
00:02:02,115 --> 00:02:06,618
it has no bearing
on her present position.

34
00:02:06,618 --> 00:02:10,043
So that has to be factored in
and understood also.

35
00:02:10,043 --> 00:02:14,669
So when we’re dealing
with devotees, particularly,

36
00:02:14,669 --> 00:02:22,306
and we don’t want to lose the grace
of the devotees and of Kṛṣṇa,

37
00:02:22,306 --> 00:02:27,395
how we view His devotees,
those who are near and dear to Him

38
00:02:27,411 --> 00:02:29,995
and those who have
dedicated their lives

39
00:02:29,995 --> 00:02:31,994
to promoting Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

40
00:02:31,994 --> 00:02:35,164
we can’t say, “Oh!
But in the background there’s this”,

41
00:02:35,164 --> 00:02:36,995
or “In the background there’s that.”

42
00:02:36,995 --> 00:02:39,567
And in this context that means

43
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:47,800
even so-called
‘observable objective criteria’

44
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:51,174
will deceive you, 
not enlighten you

45
00:02:51,174 --> 00:02:54,441
or give you a better glimpse
of who they are.

46
00:02:54,441 --> 00:02:58,196
It will actually prevent you
and deceive you

47
00:02:58,196 --> 00:03:03,323
from understanding 
who is before you.

48
00:03:03,378 --> 00:03:06,351
So that’s the nature
of spiritual culture.

